        <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <msqrt>
            <mi>n</mi>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle 2{\sqrt {n}}.}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/de5937b20291784e54b1a3ab5ec9d6cdf142a092" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -1.005ex; width:5.14ex; height:3.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle 2{\sqrt {n}}.}"></span> 
<sup id="cite&#95;ref-vk&#95;9-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-vk-9"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>9<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup><sup id="cite&#95;ref-romik&#95;2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-romik-2"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>2<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In the limit as <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle n}">
